Subject to § 22-202(b) of this article, the governmental units that are eligible to participate in the employees' systems are:
a political subdivision of the State, including:
a county;
a municipal corporation; and
a special taxing area; and
the following governmental units:
an agency on aging, as designated by the legislative body of the agency on aging;
the Allegany County Transit Authority;
subject to § 31-104 of this subtitle, the Baltimore Metropolitan Council;
a board or commission created by an Act of the General Assembly for public purpose and not for the profit of a private person;
subject to § 31-105 of this subtitle, the Canal Place Preservation and Development Authority;
the Chesapeake Bay Commission;
a cooperative library commission;
subject to § 31-103 of this subtitle, a community action agency, as designated by the legislative body of the community action agency;
a fire department that receives any of its funds from or through a county, municipal corporation, special taxing area, or other political subdivision of the State;
the Health Planning Council of Appalachia;
the Howard County Economic Development Authority;
the Interstate Commission on the Potomac River Basin;
the Lower Shore Private Industry Council, Inc.;
the Maryland Environmental Service;
subject to § 31-106 of this subtitle, the Maryland Stadium Authority;
a public library association or organization;
subject to § 31-106.2 of this subtitle, the St. Mary's Nursing Center, Inc.;
the Tri-County Council for Western Maryland, Inc.;
the Tri-County Council for Southern Maryland;
subject to § 31-107 of this subtitle, the University of Maryland Medical System Corporation;
the Upper Potomac River Commission;
subject to § 31-106.1 of this subtitle, the Maryland African American Museum Corporation; and
the Garrett County Office for Children, Youth and Families.
